    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-21T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-21T02:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-21T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 21, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 21—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 21, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>My French colleague informs me that one French and three Italian
                                Fathers and one Filipino and one Italian and four French Sisters are
                                in hands of communist bandits who recently captured Kian, Kiangsi.
                                Italian and French authorities have taken up with Chinese officials
                                matter of effecting release and I have telegraphed Lu Ti-ping at
                                Nanchang concerning release of Filipino Sister and have also
                                requested assistance of authorities here.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Martial law has been lifted from Hankow for first time since early
                                in July.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Yangtze Rapid lighter No. 1 fired upon at mileage 174 and 200
                                above Hankow by rifles and trench mortars day before
                                yesterday.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>Another bandit suppression conference will be held at Hankow in a
                                few days. Troops continue to arrive here from Honan to participate
                                in this work, the 60th and 61st Divisions having arrived
                                yesterday.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Repeated to Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
